<section id="about" class="about">
  <p class="section-label">About</p>
  <div class="prose about-prose">
    <p>
      I'm a software engineer with a decade of work across embedded systems,
      iOS SDK development, and — most recently — applied LLMs. My last few years
      have been on the iOS side of a mapping and location SDK for an automotive
      client, bridging a legacy C++ core into Swift, designing the C interface
      that connects them, and moving the SDK's rendering path off deprecated
      OpenGL.
    </p>
    <p>
      Before that I worked on hardware-adjacent products at NConcepts — Arduino
      firmware, a Qt/QML cross-platform mobile app, a desktop GUI for a
      LiDAR-based room tracker — and, further back, on backend and full-stack
      web. I like being useful across the whole stack when a problem asks for it.
    </p>
    <p>
      Outside of my day job I run <a href="/case-studies/nc-750-mirror">NC-750</a>,
      a small brand of privacy-respecting personal software, and I keep a NixOS
      homelab going (Forgejo, the *arr stack, all managed via docker-compose)
      that's where I keep my own tools honest.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

